Serialized Form

  • Package agents

    • Class agents.Message extends java.lang.Object implements Serializable

      • Serialized Fields

        • protocol

          Protocol protocol
          The protocol that the message is using. This is used in the MetaAgent's parsing of the message to decide what behaviour to use.

        • recipient

          java.lang.String recipient
          The name of the recipient of the Message. This MAY need changing to use a structure to identify inter-network level communication as well as local network, for example wrapping the sender in layers or using a complex object.

        • data

          byte[] data
          The data to be sent via the message. The data is a byte array to allow for a range of data to be sent; as sending just a string may be limiting when it comes to different uses of the system.

        • sender

          java.lang.String sender
          The name of the sender of the message. This may require the same alterations as the recipient variable to discern whether the sender is from the same network or from an inter- network level of agents.

        • flags

          int flags
          The flags for the message. This will need developing on to provide additional information about the message; such as do-not-reply, etc.

        • bounces

          int bounces
          The amount of bounces the messages can have before it dies.

    • Class agents.SystemMessage extends Message implements Serializable

      • Serialized Fields

        • action

          SystemAction action
          The action to take with this message.
          See Also:
          SystemAction
